    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Escrow, in the context of a house purchase, is essentially a neutral third party holding funds and documents until all the conditions of the sale are met, like a proper closing. Think of it like a temporary holding spot for the money and paperwork, ensuring both you and the seller are protected. It's crucial because it guarantees that the funds are only released once the property transfer is finalized, which keeps the whole transaction safe and orderly.",
