      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The money isn't just sitting in a regular bank account; it's held by a specialized escrow company or a title company. These entities are legally bound to manage the funds according to the terms of your purchase agreement. They act as the gatekeeper, ensuring that the money moves only when the agreed-upon milestones—like inspections passing or title clearing—are successfully completed. If things go wrong, the escrow agent is responsible for managing the process according to the contract, which is why they are so important.",
